parameters: "...First off. Mishiro, I think you can
probably open this big door now."
"Had no problem opening the same kind of door earlier.
Surely you can open this one if you want it."
"Before that, listen to what I have to say
now that I've got my memories back."
"I'm Ryotaro Sengoku. Younger brother of Chika Usui,
Mishiro's mother. And subordinate to her dad, Shinji Usui."
"I knew about you a while back from a New Year's card
sis sent me. To be honest, I found you cute."
"Not exactly a romantic thing, of course...
I was captivated by your latent beauty, I suppose."
"But when I asked my boss about you,
I learned you'd been glum and moping as of late."
"And I know why. You injured someone in middle school,
and sis kept you shackled ever since."
"My boss invited me over to your house,
and I was honestly pumped to try and help you."
such a beautiful girl moping around..."
"He says without a second of hesitation..."
"No poking fun, now. It's the end."
We got caught in a fire in a building at work."
After that, well, it even kind of surprised me..."
"...Partly by will, I became a soul,
and flew around to where you were... apparently."
"So for the year-or-so between my death and yours,
my spirit was sort of haunting you."
"Oh, but I was hardly even conscious of anything!
I just vaguely know that's what happened!"
"...Ahem. For you see, ever since I saw your photo,
I considered you someone beautiful and worth protecting."
"So even through death, I had the wish
of getting to talk to you at least once."
"By following you, I wound up in this world,
and in this world, my unrealized wish came true."
"Not sure if I'll ascend, or go to void, or what,
and the fact that you're dead now..."
"...I don't feel like it's irrelevant to me.
I can't say "don't blame your parents.""
"But I just want you to know. I can't force you
to understand or sympathize, but just know."
how he was spending less time with you."
you and the inheritance on a scale."
"Your mother was working with your father
to obtain "proof" that the Usui fortune belonged to them."
"Maybe she failed to control her strength properly.
Maybe she wasn't calm. But she had no ill will, I'm sure."
"I'm sure after the boss and I died, she endured the sorrow
of losing a husband and brother and fought for her family."
"Your father and mother might have been clumsy...
"I just want you to know that."
"It's probably too late to say now, though..."
"Oh, right. One last thing while I'm being late."
There are people who'd be sad about your death."
"It may be a bit warped, admittedly, but I'm one of them.
The world's not that much of a disappointment, you see."
"...So, I've done my best to encourage you."
Where should my wish to erase my existence go?"
I think you can open this big door here."
"You opened a similar door earlier, right?
I bet you can open this one too, if you try to."
"So before that, listen to what I have to -"\.\.\^
who committed suicide at 15, at Mirror Lake."
to put it bluntly, to meet a girl I loved."
"...Someone had killed her at Mirror Lake.
"So I read all these books on black magic...
And killed myself to go to the afterlife."
"To die at the same place, exactly a year later...
"I think it's a different afterlife than what the book meant,
but ultimately, I came to this world..."
"But it seems there was something to be gained here."
She was someone who "shouldn't have existed.""
"I always found it weird, and wondered why it was."
"She was born between a girl and her own father...
Between Tamaki Hinohara and Rinzou Usui."
"Can she not talk like she wants to...?"
I could get back my memories and my wish."
"And I learned about Utsuro's birth and death."
To meet Utsuro one more time."
"I've done what I needed to do in this world, so...
"It feels like it's taken so long.
But Utsuro was here before I was."
"I don't know what kind of wish you had, Utsuro..."
I'm sure it's not something simple."
"...And I'm glad that even if you're like that now,
"...She's been here for much longer than us,
and finally got her wish granted."
Is she... a soul like us, I wonder?"
"Somehow, I get the feeling she has
a close connection to this world."
"...Maybe the answer is behind this door..."
